HEADWORD: Phyllophagan
<hw>Phyl*loph"a*gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Phyllo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>fagei^n</grk> to eat.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of a group of marsupials
including the phalangists.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of a tribe of
beetles which feed upon the leaves of plants, as the chafers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phyllophagous</ent>⟦br⟧
